WEBVTT

00:12.111 --> 00:14.781
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

00:19.318 --> 00:21.187
Johnny. Hi.

00:19.318 --> 00:21.187
Hi.

00:21.721 --> 00:23.123
I'll go get Miguel.

00:23.890 --> 00:25.258
I'm not here for Miguel.

00:27.293 --> 00:29.262
<i> [HERE I GO AGAIN</i> PLAYING]

00:41.440 --> 00:45.045
<i> ♪ No, I don't know
where I'm going</i>

00:46.946 --> 00:50.283
<i> ♪ But I sure know
where I've been</i>

00:51.618 --> 00:56.322
<i>♪ Oh Lord, I pray you give me
strength to carry on</i>

00:57.322 --> 01:00.193
<i>♪ 'Cause I know what it means</i>

01:01.527 --> 01:05.498
<i> ♪ To walk along
the lonely street of dreams</i>

01:07.066 --> 01:10.370
<i> ♪ And here I go again
on my own</i>

01:11.704 --> 01:15.408
<i> ♪ Goin' down the only road
I've ever known</i>

01:16.776 --> 01:21.347
<i> ♪ Like a drifter
I was born to walk alone</i>

01:23.015 --> 01:26.519
<i> ♪ And I've made up my mind</i>

01:27.120 --> 01:28.354
<i> ♪ Baby</i>

01:28.387 --> 01:31.291
<i> ♪ And I ain't wasting
no more time</i>

01:32.858 --> 01:33.926
<i> [SONG CONTINUES ON SPEAKERS]</i>

01:33.960 --> 01:37.163
<i> ♪ And here I go again
on my own</i>

01:37.197 --> 01:39.698
<i> ♪ Goin' down the only road
I've ever known ♪</i>

01:39.732 --> 01:41.501
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:42.268 --> 01:44.170
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

01:46.239 --> 01:47.774
[RINGING STOPS]

01:46.239 --> 01:47.774
[GROANS]

01:48.674 --> 01:50.110
[SIGHS]

01:53.212 --> 01:56.048
[GASPS] He's alive.

01:56.082 --> 01:58.218
I made you some breakfast.
Bacon and eggs.

01:58.251 --> 01:59.886
I even bought you
the Minute Maid

01:59.919 --> 02:03.022
because I know you hate
the fancy stuff.

02:03.056 --> 02:04.223
Thanks, Mom.
How's the guest bedroom?

02:04.256 --> 02:05.525
You have everything
you need?

02:05.558 --> 02:08.661
No, no. It's fine.
What about you?

02:08.694 --> 02:11.330
I feel like
I'm coming down
with a fever.

02:11.363 --> 02:12.732
I don't wanna get
Amanda sick.

02:12.765 --> 02:13.766
A fever?

02:15.001 --> 02:17.870
Mmm. Fever. Right.

02:17.904 --> 02:21.740
You might wanna work on that
so you can get off the couch.

02:21.774 --> 02:23.743
I know. I'm working on it.

02:28.581 --> 02:30.550
[TRAINEES GRUNTING
IN DISTANCE]

02:39.792 --> 02:41.560
Wait. [CHUCKLES]

02:41.593 --> 02:43.563
Aren't we supposed
to be leading warm-ups?

02:45.197 --> 02:47.166
Yeah, but your grandma's
staying at the house,

02:47.199 --> 02:50.002
so this is the only
private time
we're gonna get.

02:50.035 --> 02:52.605
You know we're gonna have to
tell my parents at some point.

02:54.440 --> 02:57.744
It's just
not great timing.

02:58.711 --> 03:00.313
They're in the middle
of a fight.

03:02.948 --> 03:04.717
So we'll wait
for the right time.

03:09.422 --> 03:10.790
DEMETRI:
Hey, guys, check it out!

03:17.596 --> 03:21.667
Look what I found.
It was just sitting
in these rocks.

03:21.701 --> 03:24.437
Is that Mr. Miyagi's
Medal of Honor?

03:24.470 --> 03:27.306
That's crazy. We looked
all over for this.

03:27.339 --> 03:28.708
Huh. Must have been here
the whole time.

03:40.153 --> 03:42.522
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

03:42.555 --> 03:44.556
Did you see
how she looked at me
when I said, "Two lumps"?

03:44.590 --> 03:45.892
[GIGGLES]

03:48.327 --> 03:50.095
Oh, good morning.
Are you heading out?

03:50.129 --> 03:51.630
I think Miguel left already.

03:51.663 --> 03:54.801
Oh, yeah, yeah.
Just, uh, on my way, so...

03:56.268 --> 03:58.638
Johnny, uh, this is Graham.

04:01.573 --> 04:03.710
Pleased to meet you, mate.
Oh.

04:03.743 --> 04:06.746
Cracking strong grip.
Best take me in for X-rays.

04:06.779 --> 04:10.616
[CHUCKLES]
Isn't he funny?

04:06.779 --> 04:10.616
Yeah, he's very...

04:10.650 --> 04:14.487
[SIGHS] Well, see you
later, Johnny.

04:10.650 --> 04:14.487
All right, I'll see you later.

04:14.520 --> 04:16.322
He teaches
my son karate.

04:17.757 --> 04:19.525
[DOOR OPENS]

04:24.964 --> 04:26.733
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

04:33.706 --> 04:34.807
Wow.

04:34.840 --> 04:38.277
Is that lunch
from Sugar Fish?
And look at that.

04:38.311 --> 04:40.446
Matcha green tea
from Urth Caffe.

04:40.479 --> 04:42.648
Someone must have trekked
over the hill.

04:42.682 --> 04:44.917
Thank you.
But I actually...

04:44.950 --> 04:46.885
And before you even bring up
the inventory statements,

04:46.919 --> 04:49.389
I've already taken them
off your plate.
I finished them an hour ago.

04:49.422 --> 04:53.225
So, I don't know about you,
but that toro right there
is calling my name.

04:53.258 --> 04:57.329
I've got a lunch
with the sales team
over at Woodland Hills.

04:57.363 --> 05:00.700
It's on our joint calendar.
But, um, you enjoy.

05:02.268 --> 05:05.371
But it's a lot of sushi.

05:05.404 --> 05:07.940
Share it
with the customers.

05:07.973 --> 05:11.343
Hey. There's free sushi
in there if you're hungry.

05:11.376 --> 05:13.245
WOMAN: Thank you.

05:13.279 --> 05:15.381
MIGUEL: What about Friday?

05:13.279 --> 05:15.381
TORY: I can't.

05:15.415 --> 05:16.582
I'm working
at the roller rink.

05:16.616 --> 05:18.017
Great. Let's turn it
into a date night.

05:18.050 --> 05:20.719
[CHUCKLES] Candlelit dinner
at the snack bar on my break?

05:20.753 --> 05:23.789
Look, there's nothing more
romantic than free hot dogs
and chicken nugs.

05:23.822 --> 05:27.560
Free? Not for you.
You gotta pay up.

05:23.822 --> 05:27.560
I'll splurge.

05:27.593 --> 05:30.662
All right. But you gotta wear
a costume. It's '80s night.

05:30.696 --> 05:32.498
Are you kidding?
I love the '80s.

05:32.531 --> 05:34.600
Dibs on Anthony Michael Hall
in<i> Weird Science.</i>

05:34.634 --> 05:36.669
I don't think you have
to call dibs on that.

05:39.972 --> 05:41.107
One second.

05:44.210 --> 05:45.411
Hey.

05:44.210 --> 05:45.411
What's up?

05:46.145 --> 05:47.780
About Coyote Creek,
we cool?

05:47.813 --> 05:51.551
[SCOFFS] We were enemies
for a day,
but Cobra Kai for life.

06:06.665 --> 06:08.668
[GRUNTS]

06:06.665 --> 06:08.668
Everybody, fall in.

06:15.841 --> 06:18.110
Today, we'll be learning
one of the most
important lessons

06:18.143 --> 06:19.512
a Cobra Kai
could ever know.

06:19.545 --> 06:20.979
Where's Sensei Kreese?

06:21.013 --> 06:24.384
Shouldn't we wait for
the sensei emeritus
before we get going?

06:26.185 --> 06:28.387
[EXHALES] Or not.

06:28.420 --> 06:30.022
Mr. Kreese will no longer
be joining us.

06:32.291 --> 06:33.559
BOY: Seriously?

06:35.761 --> 06:38.263
I made a promise
when I became your sensei.

06:38.297 --> 06:39.966
To always look out
for your best interests.

06:40.966 --> 06:43.469
Despite how hard
this may be for all of us,

06:44.604 --> 06:46.639
he didn't have
our best interests at heart.

06:47.673 --> 06:49.942
John Kreese may have
founded Cobra Kai,

06:49.976 --> 06:53.045
but he no longer represents
what this dojo stands for.

06:54.713 --> 06:57.750
His Cobra Kai was old
and outdated.

06:59.618 --> 07:02.622
He refused to move forward,
and what happens
when we do that, Mr. Diaz?

07:03.623 --> 07:06.058
You get stuck like cement.

07:03.623 --> 07:06.058
Exactly.

07:07.093 --> 07:09.796
To be a great fighter,
you gotta learn to adapt.

07:12.197 --> 07:14.433
This creed on the wall...

07:14.466 --> 07:18.004
Follow it to the letter,
it'll make you strong.

07:19.271 --> 07:20.840
It'll make you formidable.

07:23.842 --> 07:25.878
It'll also make you an asshole.

07:30.015 --> 07:32.151
'Cause that's just black paint
on a white wall.

07:33.418 --> 07:35.221
But life's not
black and white.

07:37.089 --> 07:38.991
More often than not,
it's gray.

07:41.093 --> 07:42.628
And it's in those gray areas

07:42.661 --> 07:44.864
where Johnny Lawrence's
Cobra Kai

07:46.098 --> 07:48.167
sometimes shows mercy.

07:50.069 --> 07:53.172
Doesn't mean you can't
be badass. It's still
a requirement.

07:53.205 --> 07:55.708
But you have to learn to think,
not just with your gut,

07:57.043 --> 07:58.578
or your fists,

08:00.479 --> 08:03.115
but to really use this.

08:06.886 --> 08:09.088
Which leads me
to today's lesson.

08:12.524 --> 08:13.859
[STUDENTS CHUCKLE]

08:13.892 --> 08:15.027
Headbutting.

08:16.128 --> 08:17.196
Grab a partner.

08:18.297 --> 08:19.832
[GROANS]

08:19.865 --> 08:22.134
That was awesome.
Do me next.

08:23.602 --> 08:25.037
[RAYMOND GROANS]

08:27.072 --> 08:28.607
Hey, uh, Sensei.

08:28.640 --> 08:30.142
Just tuck in your chin
and aim for the nose

08:30.176 --> 08:32.111
with the crown of your head.
It's not that hard.

08:32.144 --> 08:35.114
No, it's not about headbutting.
I think I got that down.

08:35.147 --> 08:37.516
It's about Sensei Kreese.

08:35.147 --> 08:37.516
What about him?

08:37.550 --> 08:40.419
I know he's your friend,
so if you wanna talk...

08:40.452 --> 08:42.888
You don't have to
worry about me.

08:42.921 --> 08:45.157
Besides, you should be focused
on that girlfriend of yours.

08:46.492 --> 08:49.028
You know about that?

08:46.492 --> 08:49.028
I'm not blind.

08:49.061 --> 08:51.029
Just don't get distracted.

08:49.061 --> 08:51.029
Yeah.

08:51.063 --> 08:53.665
All right? You can play
"hide the plantain"
on your own time.

08:53.699 --> 08:56.202
But in class,
I need you focused.

08:53.699 --> 08:56.202
Yes, Sensei.

08:57.136 --> 08:59.004
What about you?
Do you have any, uh...

08:59.037 --> 09:01.173
Don't worry about me,
all right?
I do just fine.

09:01.207 --> 09:02.775
Okay.

09:02.808 --> 09:04.843
If you wanted to,
I could set you up
on an app.

09:04.877 --> 09:06.978
That's how my mom
found her boyfriend.

09:07.012 --> 09:09.481
Yeah, how's that going?

09:07.012 --> 09:09.481
It's going well.

09:09.514 --> 09:12.551
She's had some pretty bad luck
with guys, so it's nice to see
her happy.

09:12.584 --> 09:14.554
That's good.
I'm glad to hear that.

09:16.688 --> 09:21.059
So, uh, all right,
what's the deal
with this app thing?

09:21.093 --> 09:23.262
AMANDA: So, we have
some new cars
on the showroom floor.

09:23.296 --> 09:26.999
Let's get the detail guys
in here because they can
never be too...

09:27.032 --> 09:28.167
...clean.

09:27.032 --> 09:28.167
DANIEL: All right.

09:28.200 --> 09:30.069
Here you go. No, no.
Demetri, you know this.

09:30.102 --> 09:33.605
Wax on with the right hand,
counter-clockwise
with the left.

09:33.638 --> 09:35.241
Watch Demetri.
He's got it.

09:36.208 --> 09:37.343
Not bad, right?

09:38.377 --> 09:40.179
Child labor.
That's a bold move.

09:40.212 --> 09:42.581
It's crazy no one's
ever thought of it.

09:42.614 --> 09:44.083
Ten more minutes
of training, okay?

09:44.116 --> 09:47.620
Wait, wait. No, no.
It's not training.
This is me trying to help.

09:48.086 --> 09:49.488
Say I'm sorry.

09:49.522 --> 09:51.456
What else can I do, Amanda?

09:51.490 --> 09:54.159
It's not a puzzle, Daniel.

09:54.192 --> 09:59.131
Look, I don't wanna fight.
I just know that
this is not permanent.

09:59.164 --> 10:00.199
Neither is sushi.

10:00.232 --> 10:02.468
You can't put a Band-Aid
on an open head wound.

10:02.501 --> 10:04.903
Our marriage
is an open head wound?

10:04.936 --> 10:08.341
Pick whatever
analogy you want.
You know what I mean.

10:14.513 --> 10:17.583
Okay. The app is downloaded.

10:17.616 --> 10:19.751
What type of women
are you looking to meet?

10:19.785 --> 10:21.920
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING
ON SPEAKERS]

10:21.954 --> 10:25.691
Super hot babes. Dumb question.
Okay, what are your likes?

10:25.724 --> 10:27.193
My likes?

10:25.724 --> 10:27.193
Mmm-hmm.

10:27.226 --> 10:29.227
What am I supposed to say?
Long walks on the beach?

10:29.261 --> 10:33.065
I like muscle cars,
martial arts
and<i> Iron Eagle.</i>

10:33.098 --> 10:35.000
And<i> Iron Eagle II.</i>

10:35.034 --> 10:37.903
Why aren't you texting
this down? Computer dating
was your idea.

10:37.937 --> 10:40.072
Look, you have to
take this seriously.

10:40.106 --> 10:41.306
It used to be simple.

10:41.339 --> 10:44.609
Find a chick in a bar.
Bump into her hard,
but not too hard.

10:44.643 --> 10:47.680
Pretty hard.
Then you buy her a beer.

10:44.643 --> 10:47.680
No.

10:47.713 --> 10:50.682
Tried and true, Diaz.
That's how the cavemen did it.

10:50.715 --> 10:52.217
Cavemen. That's another like.

10:52.251 --> 10:54.720
Like the ones in those
insurance commercials.

10:54.754 --> 10:58.190
[SIGHS] I think I can fill out
the rest of this on my own.

10:58.223 --> 11:00.659
What about clothes?
What are you wearing?

11:00.692 --> 11:02.795
You gonna teach me
about fashion now?

11:03.595 --> 11:04.864
Might have to.

11:12.237 --> 11:13.105
Okay.

11:15.640 --> 11:18.277
So, I was thinking
a buttoned-up shirt
and some distressed jeans.

11:18.310 --> 11:19.778
You have any of those?

11:19.812 --> 11:22.314
I have old jeans,
if that's what you're saying.

11:22.348 --> 11:23.916
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

11:23.949 --> 11:27.452
Hey. There's a chick
on my app.

11:27.485 --> 11:29.121
MIGUEL: Yeah, look, all right.

11:29.154 --> 11:31.023
Just swipe right if you
like her and we'll set up
a bunch of dates.

11:31.056 --> 11:34.126
This is dumb. You can't find
anything out about a chick
from one look...

11:34.160 --> 11:35.461
Ooh, this one's hot.

11:37.429 --> 11:39.097
Hey, can I borrow this jacket?

11:39.130 --> 11:40.266
Huh?

11:41.267 --> 11:42.435
Yeah, whatever.

11:43.135 --> 11:44.636
No.

11:44.669 --> 11:47.106
No. Not with a ten-foot pole.

11:47.840 --> 11:49.408
Lose that mole, you're in.

11:50.575 --> 11:52.244
Eh. Actually, yes.

11:57.215 --> 11:58.451
LUCILLE: Hey, Sammy.

11:59.651 --> 12:01.787
Come help me
with the groceries.

12:03.822 --> 12:06.825
Oh. I didn't realize
you were both here.

12:06.858 --> 12:08.827
Hi, Mrs. LaRusso.

12:06.858 --> 12:08.827
Hi.

12:08.861 --> 12:12.331
I got a couple more bags
in the car.
Be a help, will you?

12:16.668 --> 12:18.337
Unless we wanna keep
avoiding your family,

12:18.370 --> 12:20.473
we should probably go out
one of these nights.

12:22.942 --> 12:25.711
WOMAN: My oldest is eight,
and I also have
a 4-year-old.

12:25.744 --> 12:27.679
There they are.

12:25.744 --> 12:27.679
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

12:27.713 --> 12:29.582
Oh, they're so cute.

12:27.713 --> 12:29.582
Thanks.

12:29.615 --> 12:32.117
It's tough trying to meet
someone who likes to have fun,

12:32.150 --> 12:34.186
but also knows
how to handle kids.

12:34.219 --> 12:36.955
With my job,
I'm around kids
all the time, so...

12:36.989 --> 12:38.523
Believe me, I know
how to handle them.

12:38.556 --> 12:40.091
That is so good to hear.

12:40.125 --> 12:42.995
This one time, this kid
in my class was texting
on his phone.

12:43.028 --> 12:45.164
Mmm-hmm.

12:43.028 --> 12:45.164
So I body-slammed him

12:45.197 --> 12:47.399
into the mat,
flying elbow to his teeth.

12:47.432 --> 12:49.200
[JOHNNY CHUCKLES]

12:49.234 --> 12:51.770
One sec. I gotta read
this email real quick.

12:51.804 --> 12:52.871
You can read your email
on that thing?

12:52.905 --> 12:55.174
Yeah. You've never seen
a smartwatch?

12:55.207 --> 12:57.075
Oh, smartwatch.

12:57.108 --> 12:59.845
Yeah. I read my emails
all the time.

13:00.412 --> 13:01.847
In my smartphone.

13:03.248 --> 13:04.517
It's an Ericsson.

13:04.550 --> 13:08.053
I try to stay active
in a variety of organizations.

13:08.086 --> 13:10.589
We combat all institutions
of oppression.

13:10.622 --> 13:15.093
Runaway capitalism,
climate change denial,
the patriarchy.

13:15.127 --> 13:18.496
The problem is, a lot of these
issues are becoming systemic.

13:18.530 --> 13:20.532
Oh, yeah.
Totally systemic.

13:20.565 --> 13:22.067
I hate the Patriots, too.

13:22.100 --> 13:23.935
Listen, what do you say
we quit the chit-chat,

13:23.969 --> 13:25.671
and hop in my Challenger?

13:25.704 --> 13:29.074
Teach you how to drive a stick.
If you know what I mean.

13:31.643 --> 13:35.247
Johnny, right? Sorry I'm late.
The traffic on the 101
was just...

13:36.548 --> 13:38.783
Wait. Have we met before?

13:38.817 --> 13:40.219
I don't know.

13:40.752 --> 13:42.087
Hold on.

13:42.121 --> 13:45.591
You're that dumb asshole who
hung my TV on the wrong wall.

13:46.692 --> 13:48.694
You never told me
which wall to put it on.

13:48.727 --> 13:50.429
Because of you,
I got fired.

13:50.462 --> 13:51.930
You called me a bitch!

13:51.963 --> 13:53.365
No, I said you were
bitching at me!

13:53.398 --> 13:56.502
You know what? That's it.
I'm done
with these shitty apps.

13:58.570 --> 13:59.572
Bitch.

14:20.626 --> 14:22.361
What's this?

14:22.394 --> 14:25.463
Ah, just taking a walk
down memory lane.

14:25.497 --> 14:26.865
[CHUCKLES]

14:26.898 --> 14:28.900
A scrapbook? [CHUCKLES]

14:28.934 --> 14:31.270
I thought everything was
in the cloud now.

14:32.070 --> 14:33.839
I'll digitize it
sooner or later.

14:33.872 --> 14:36.975
It's just, something
about these old pictures.

14:37.008 --> 14:40.512
Looking at them on your phone
just doesn't do them justice,
you know?

14:40.546 --> 14:41.947
Very true.

14:42.648 --> 14:45.083
Ooh, you got
some good ones.

14:45.117 --> 14:48.387
Look at my hair. The '80s!

14:48.420 --> 14:50.022
[CHUCKLES]

14:48.420 --> 14:50.022
Oh, man.

14:56.528 --> 14:57.663
It'll get better.

14:58.630 --> 15:00.232
She'll come around.

15:00.799 --> 15:02.101
[SIGHING] I know, Ma.

15:03.168 --> 15:05.671
I've tried every grand gesture
I could think of.

15:06.905 --> 15:08.173
[SIGHS]

15:11.610 --> 15:13.145
Remember Coney Island?

15:14.913 --> 15:16.916
It's about the best day
of my life.

15:17.549 --> 15:18.517
Dad and I ate something

15:18.550 --> 15:22.087
from every booth
on the row. Nathan's...

15:22.120 --> 15:24.322
Cotton candy,
frozen custard,
you name it.

15:24.356 --> 15:26.758
He still took me
on the Cyclone
five times in a row.

15:26.792 --> 15:28.627
[CHUCKLES]
That sounds like him.

15:34.365 --> 15:37.036
It was about the time
he started getting sick.

15:37.602 --> 15:38.604
[SIGHS]

15:41.339 --> 15:44.276
You know what I remember?

15:41.339 --> 15:44.276
What?

15:45.410 --> 15:47.645
What do you call...
What was it, uh...

15:47.679 --> 15:50.549
"The Wonder Wheel."
That's what it was.

15:47.679 --> 15:50.549
Oh, yeah.

15:50.582 --> 15:52.050
My God.
That amazing view.

15:52.083 --> 15:55.254
No. No, no, no. The line.

15:56.688 --> 15:58.223
That's what I remember.

15:58.257 --> 16:02.227
It wasn't the lights,
it wasn't the ride.

16:03.095 --> 16:05.130
It was the smallest moment.

16:06.531 --> 16:10.402
We were waiting in line
on the Wonder Wheel,

16:11.169 --> 16:14.006
and, uh... Just us.

16:15.039 --> 16:18.010
And Dad held my hand

16:19.244 --> 16:22.281
and he put his head
on my shoulder.

16:24.449 --> 16:25.517
Right here.

16:27.151 --> 16:30.488
And he told me
he loved me.

16:30.522 --> 16:31.523
[CHUCKLES]

16:33.892 --> 16:38.497
I could still feel his hair
on my cheek.

16:44.069 --> 16:46.372
That's all I ever wanted
to know.

16:47.272 --> 16:49.775
That he was in it with me.

16:50.843 --> 16:52.344
No matter what.

16:54.680 --> 16:55.681
[SNICKERS]

17:00.985 --> 17:02.388
I love you.

17:03.021 --> 17:04.590
Love you, Ma.

17:06.191 --> 17:07.226
[ROCK SONG PLAYING]

17:07.259 --> 17:09.728
<i> ♪ I got it so bad</i>

17:11.996 --> 17:15.200
<i> ♪ I just want to say that</i>

17:17.603 --> 17:21.273
<i> ♪ I swear I can't hide</i>

17:22.107 --> 17:24.842
<i> ♪ How I feel about you</i>

17:24.876 --> 17:27.745
<i> ♪ How I feel about you</i>

17:27.779 --> 17:30.682
<i> ♪ How I feel about you</i>

17:30.716 --> 17:33.152
<i> ♪ How I feel about you ♪</i>

17:33.418 --> 17:34.820
[SIGHS]

17:36.588 --> 17:41.460
Hey, it's been a long time.
But just signed up
on the Facebook.

17:41.493 --> 17:46.331
It's an app on my smartphone.
Maybe we connect
one of these days?

17:47.598 --> 17:48.767
Johnny.

17:54.806 --> 17:56.408
Nah, too desperate.

17:58.110 --> 17:59.544
Hey.

17:58.110 --> 17:59.544
[CELL PHONE CHIMES]

17:59.577 --> 18:02.848
Shit. Sorry about that.

17:59.577 --> 18:02.848
It's all right. No sweat.

18:02.881 --> 18:05.651
Let me make it up to you.
Buy you another Banquet?

18:07.352 --> 18:08.320
Yeah.

18:09.120 --> 18:11.523
<i> [DANCE HALL DAYS</i> PLAYING]

18:13.591 --> 18:16.228
<i> ♪ Take your baby
by the hand</i>

18:18.229 --> 18:20.698
<i> ♪ And make her do
a high handstand ♪</i>

18:20.732 --> 18:22.401
[CHUCKLES]

18:22.434 --> 18:25.670
Gotta say, I wasn't sure
about the costumes,

18:25.704 --> 18:28.406
but it's definitely nice not
having to sneak around.

18:28.440 --> 18:29.774
I still think
you should have dressed

18:29.808 --> 18:31.142
like Andrew McCarthy
for synergy,

18:31.176 --> 18:32.577
or at least Duckie.

18:32.610 --> 18:35.681
Come on. With the hair,
you know my only option
was Spader.

18:37.483 --> 18:38.383
I'm starving.

18:38.416 --> 18:40.586
Oh, excuse me.
Can we get some menus?

18:42.588 --> 18:44.556
Oh. Look who it is.

18:45.157 --> 18:46.324
[STAMMERS]

18:46.357 --> 18:47.959
I didn't know
you worked here.

18:47.993 --> 18:51.162
Yeah, well, not all of us
get to use
Daddy's credit card.

18:51.196 --> 18:54.132
Look, we just wanted
to order some food.
I'm sorry.

18:54.165 --> 18:55.600
What time do you go
on break?

18:55.634 --> 18:58.303
I wanted to time it out
so that the fries
are actually crispy.

18:59.704 --> 19:01.073
Oh. Um...

19:01.106 --> 19:02.774
Hey, I didn't
recognize you. I...

19:03.875 --> 19:06.478
Dig the costumes.

19:03.875 --> 19:06.478
Thanks.

19:07.312 --> 19:11.149
Uh, Tory,
this is Sam and Robby.

19:11.182 --> 19:12.651
Yeah, we've met already.

19:12.684 --> 19:15.387
Sam and I had a little run-in
at the beach club.

19:12.684 --> 19:15.387
Oh.

19:17.021 --> 19:18.924
So, how do you two know
each other?

19:19.757 --> 19:21.927
Tory's in Cobra Kai.

19:22.794 --> 19:24.830
Figures.

19:22.794 --> 19:24.830
What was that?

19:25.964 --> 19:27.565
Nothing.

19:27.599 --> 19:30.669
All right, I gotta
get back to work.
See you later, babe.

19:38.442 --> 19:40.779
Come on.
Let's get some skates.

19:44.682 --> 19:47.352
I swear, she's sitting there
tapping on her watch,

19:47.385 --> 19:48.653
like she's in frikking
<i>Knight Rider.</i>

19:48.686 --> 19:49.955
"K.I.T.T., where the hell
are you?"

19:50.488 --> 19:52.090
[LAUGHS]

19:52.123 --> 19:54.926
People now. I ditched
the apps completely.

19:54.960 --> 19:58.130
Yeah, all this nerd technology
messes with your head.

19:58.163 --> 19:59.631
It used to be simple.

20:00.164 --> 20:01.233
Like...

20:02.400 --> 20:03.969
...this.

20:02.400 --> 20:03.969
Yeah.

20:05.604 --> 20:06.538
Like this.

20:10.708 --> 20:14.546
I'm gonna go to the bathroom.
Can you, uh, get me another?

20:14.879 --> 20:15.747
Sure.

20:17.548 --> 20:19.550
What about that girl
you were telling me about?

20:19.584 --> 20:21.753
GRAHAM: Yeah, I'm seeing her
later tonight.

20:19.584 --> 20:21.753
Hmm.

20:21.786 --> 20:26.124
Mate, I'm telling you,
you should see her apartment.
She lives with her mum.

20:26.157 --> 20:27.359
Really?

20:27.392 --> 20:29.160
Way I see it, she's good
for a few bangs

20:29.194 --> 20:30.528
and then I'll drop her.

20:29.194 --> 20:30.528
[CHUCKLES]

20:30.562 --> 20:33.532
I mean, I'm not trying to be
a dad to her kid or anything.

20:35.767 --> 20:37.002
Hey there, beautiful.

20:45.410 --> 20:48.013
Everything okay?

20:45.410 --> 20:48.013
Yeah.

20:49.714 --> 20:53.318
Okay, I'll admit,
it's kinda weird
running into your ex.

20:53.351 --> 20:55.587
Plus, that girl Tory
is the worst.

20:57.455 --> 21:01.026
Remember what your dad says.
"There's good in everyone."

21:01.059 --> 21:03.695
She just has to be shown
the right way.

21:03.729 --> 21:06.031
But if you want to
kick her ass,
I won't stop you.

21:06.064 --> 21:07.899
[BOTH LAUGH]

21:07.932 --> 21:10.135
<i> [IF YOU LEAVE</i> PLAYING]

21:10.168 --> 21:13.271
Oh, no way.
Oh, that's too perfect.

21:13.304 --> 21:15.307
I might have said something
to the DJ.

21:15.340 --> 21:18.877
That is such a Duckie move.
You're a Duckie
in Spader clothing.

21:20.846 --> 21:21.846
[SKATE SQUEAK]

21:21.879 --> 21:24.950
Whoa, are you okay?

21:21.879 --> 21:24.950
Crap, my skate broke.

21:26.151 --> 21:29.021
Uh, I'll be right back.
I'll come find you.

21:26.151 --> 21:29.021
Okay.

21:30.555 --> 21:34.358
<i> ♪ If you leave
Don't leave now</i>

21:34.392 --> 21:36.895
<i> ♪ Please don't take
my heart away ♪</i>

21:36.928 --> 21:37.896
Hey.

21:39.363 --> 21:40.699
What do you want?

21:40.732 --> 21:42.634
I think my skates
are too big.

21:44.136 --> 21:45.537
Look, about Tory...

21:45.570 --> 21:47.506
I can't believe you could be
with a girl like that.

21:49.174 --> 21:52.610
You don't even know her.

21:49.174 --> 21:52.610
I know enough.

21:52.643 --> 21:57.449
Three hot dogs,
two vanilla shakes
and a Coke with extra ice.

22:01.653 --> 22:03.322
I should be the one
that's pissed off.

22:04.522 --> 22:06.491
Here you are, making me think
I'm a paranoid asshole

22:06.525 --> 22:08.092
and yet you're on a date
with Robby?

22:08.126 --> 22:09.561
It's not a date.

22:12.830 --> 22:14.833
Not a date. Yeah.

22:15.600 --> 22:17.602
Heard that one before.

22:18.636 --> 22:20.671
Look, I just came
to clear the air

22:20.705 --> 22:22.441
so that things
wouldn't be weird.

22:23.475 --> 22:25.010
I guess that's a lost cause.

22:31.382 --> 22:33.050
Thanks.

22:33.084 --> 22:35.620
But I told him,
"It better be a Harley
or I'm not getting on."

22:36.588 --> 22:37.923
Yeah, I'm the same way.

22:37.956 --> 22:39.491
MELISSA: So, what kind of car
do you drive anyway?

22:40.358 --> 22:41.760
I'm a Mustang
kind of girl, so...

22:41.793 --> 22:43.662
GRAHAM: Be right back,
darling.

22:41.793 --> 22:43.662
WOMAN: I'll be right here.

22:46.264 --> 22:48.033
Bloody hell.

22:48.066 --> 22:49.901
America's falling apart.

22:51.236 --> 22:52.671
MELISSA: Hey, you wanna
get some food?

22:52.704 --> 22:54.539
I know a good burger joint.

22:52.704 --> 22:54.539
[SIGHS]

22:57.208 --> 22:59.511
I'm sorry. I have to go.

23:01.847 --> 23:03.415
What?
Don't you want my number?

23:05.383 --> 23:07.085
[URINATING]

23:05.383 --> 23:07.085
[GRUNTS]

23:10.355 --> 23:12.790
Go on. Room for one more.

23:12.824 --> 23:14.693
[ZIPS ZIPPER]

23:12.824 --> 23:14.693
Hey, man.

23:16.194 --> 23:18.663
I heard what you said
about Carmen.

23:18.696 --> 23:21.165
If you gonna do that,
just break it up
with her, all right?

23:21.199 --> 23:24.302
Oh, you're the neighbor,
aren't you?
You fancy her, mate?

23:24.335 --> 23:28.073
[SCOFFS] Cheers for the advice.
I've got some advice for you.

23:28.106 --> 23:29.173
Bugger off!

23:29.207 --> 23:30.709
[GROANING]

23:33.811 --> 23:34.813
[GRUNTS]

23:35.312 --> 23:36.181
No, no!

23:37.849 --> 23:39.151
You're lucky
I'm showing mercy.

23:40.918 --> 23:42.120
This is mercy?

23:43.054 --> 23:45.323
Never go near Carmen again.
Do you understand?

23:45.356 --> 23:47.192
Whatever you say.
I'll ghost her.

23:47.225 --> 23:49.528
You'll what?

23:47.225 --> 23:49.528
I'll leave her alone,
I'll disappear.

23:50.128 --> 23:51.163
Damn right you will.

23:55.299 --> 23:56.168
Mate.

24:03.008 --> 24:06.444
[SIGHS] I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to...

24:06.477 --> 24:08.847
Oh. Hey, Robby.

24:06.477 --> 24:08.847
Hey.

24:08.880 --> 24:11.582
So, I've gotten
two compliments
on my outfit.

24:11.616 --> 24:14.152
But everyone thinks
I'm some guy
named Dan Johnson.

24:14.185 --> 24:17.455
You ever heard of him?

24:14.185 --> 24:17.455
Uh, no.

24:17.488 --> 24:19.458
I'm sure whoever he is,
he's cute.

24:20.291 --> 24:21.392
[GROANS]

24:21.425 --> 24:23.094
ROBBY: Are you okay?

24:21.425 --> 24:23.094
Oops.

24:23.128 --> 24:24.095
Sorry, princess.

24:27.732 --> 24:29.500
ROBBY: Sam!

24:27.732 --> 24:29.500
[TORY GASPS]

24:29.534 --> 24:31.169
[ALL EXCLAIM]

24:32.703 --> 24:35.073
What the hell, Sam?

24:32.703 --> 24:35.073
What? Me...

24:35.106 --> 24:36.074
Are you okay,
Tory?

24:37.475 --> 24:38.543
Thanks.

24:38.576 --> 24:40.778
All right, you're done.
You're out.

24:40.811 --> 24:42.714
She's the one
who started it.

24:40.811 --> 24:42.714
You're out.

25:01.233 --> 25:02.334
What is this?

25:02.367 --> 25:04.636
You shouldn't be
working this late.

25:04.669 --> 25:08.639
Yeah, well, with Anoush gone,
somebody has to review
today's transactions.

25:08.672 --> 25:10.541
I want you
to forget about that

25:10.574 --> 25:12.611
and I want you to remember
something else.

25:13.911 --> 25:18.116
Sixteen years ago,
grand opening party.
Remember?

25:19.417 --> 25:20.785
Is this a sobriety test?

25:20.819 --> 25:23.221
Oh, come on, you remember.
Play along.

25:24.155 --> 25:25.790
Our first big opening.

25:32.763 --> 25:35.066
Enjoy the party.
Buy a car!

25:36.400 --> 25:37.368
Come with me.

25:37.402 --> 25:39.003
Where are we going?

25:37.402 --> 25:39.003
Come on.

25:39.037 --> 25:40.272
Oh, okay.

25:42.507 --> 25:44.042
Mmm.

25:42.507 --> 25:44.042
[EXHALES]

25:44.075 --> 25:44.943
Here we go.

25:44.976 --> 25:46.378
What, you trying
to torture me?

25:46.411 --> 25:48.779
Nah. Don't worry.
It's sparkling cider.

25:48.813 --> 25:49.948
Ooh.

25:52.217 --> 25:55.120
Well, we're ditching
our own grand opening party,

25:55.153 --> 25:56.988
we better be drinking
to something good.

25:57.322 --> 25:58.723
How about,

25:59.590 --> 26:01.326
to finally having

26:02.060 --> 26:03.294
something that's ours?

26:03.327 --> 26:05.296
But what about
this little one?

26:05.329 --> 26:09.434
What, her? No, no. She's mine.
You can have the next one.

26:05.329 --> 26:09.434
[LAUGHS]

26:09.467 --> 26:11.736
Okay, to something
that's ours.

26:16.207 --> 26:17.742
Mmm.

26:17.775 --> 26:19.010
How about some music?

26:19.043 --> 26:20.111
Mmm-hmm.

26:22.480 --> 26:24.682
<i> [YOU'RE THE INSPIRATION</i>
PLAYING]

26:24.715 --> 26:27.218
Wow. You really
prepared for this.

26:28.386 --> 26:29.688
You have no idea.

26:33.291 --> 26:36.928
Don't tell me
this is the same cider.

26:33.291 --> 26:36.928
No way.

26:37.695 --> 26:41.299
This is the good stuff.

26:41.332 --> 26:44.903
<i> ♪ You know our love
was meant to be ♪</i>

26:47.037 --> 26:50.675
So, this was
the grand plan, huh?
Trip down memory lane?

26:51.442 --> 26:52.611
It's not bad.

26:53.711 --> 26:55.880
It was a good night
for the dealership.

26:57.615 --> 26:58.984
Forget the dealership.

26:59.850 --> 27:01.786
What I remember most
about that night

27:01.819 --> 27:03.921
was sitting in the back seat
of that car,

27:03.954 --> 27:06.157
just you and me
mapping out our future.

27:08.893 --> 27:12.931
[SIGHS] Look. I know I've been
MIA the last few months.

27:14.532 --> 27:16.768
Part of it was Cobra Kai.

27:16.801 --> 27:20.939
Part of it was
missing Mr. Miyagi.

27:22.373 --> 27:23.708
Opening up that dojo

27:23.742 --> 27:26.344
definitely made it feel like
he was back in my life again.

27:28.212 --> 27:29.247
I know.

27:30.214 --> 27:32.317
And I don't want you
to have to give that up.

27:33.651 --> 27:36.755
But I also know
if he was here right now,

27:37.889 --> 27:39.791
he would tell me,
"Forget about karate.

27:41.526 --> 27:43.061
"Focus on what's important."

27:44.429 --> 27:45.764
Oh, yeah?

27:46.197 --> 27:47.666
And what's that?

27:48.432 --> 27:51.902
<i> ♪ In my heart
In my soul</i>

27:51.936 --> 27:54.972
<i> ♪ You're the meaning
in my life</i>

27:55.005 --> 27:58.509
<i> ♪ You're the inspiration</i>

27:58.543 --> 28:01.712
<i>♪ You bring feeling to my life</i>

28:01.745 --> 28:05.750
<i> ♪ You're the inspiration</i>

28:05.783 --> 28:08.052
<i> ♪ Wanna have you near me</i>

28:08.085 --> 28:11.856
<i> ♪ I wanna have you
hear me sayin' ♪</i>

28:16.427 --> 28:17.696
CARMEN: Hi, Johnny.

28:18.796 --> 28:21.031
Hey, how you doing?

28:21.065 --> 28:24.703
I, uh, was supposed
to go out with Graham,

28:25.903 --> 28:27.772
but looks like
he stood me up.

28:28.072 --> 28:29.307
Oh.

28:30.341 --> 28:31.710
Forget about him.

28:33.611 --> 28:34.979
You don't deserve
a loser like that.

28:36.280 --> 28:38.249
You deserve a guy
that at least shows up.

28:39.283 --> 28:41.853
Anybody'd be lucky
to go on a date with you.

28:42.753 --> 28:44.155
You asking me out?

28:46.658 --> 28:47.859
What if I am?

29:01.105 --> 29:02.941
CARMEN:<i> So, how's Miguel's
training going?</i>

29:02.974 --> 29:05.142
He's on the right path.
You should be proud.

29:05.176 --> 29:08.446
He has this new girlfriend.
I can't keep up with
all the drama.

29:08.479 --> 29:10.781
SAM:<i> I just don't understand
what Miguel sees in her.</i>

29:10.815 --> 29:13.117
At least you both
moved on, right?

29:10.815 --> 29:13.117
Yeah.

29:13.150 --> 29:15.520
<i> Why don't you come over later?
It should be wild.</i>

29:16.187 --> 29:17.889
[ALL CHEERING]

29:18.722 --> 29:19.757
Oh, come on.

29:19.790 --> 29:20.992
You gotta be kidding me.

29:21.025 --> 29:22.760
DANIEL:<i> What the hell
is your problem?</i>

29:22.793 --> 29:25.396
JOHNNY:<i> You, LaRusso.
You've been a major pain
in my ass all summer.</i>

29:25.430 --> 29:27.465
BOY:<i> Come on!</i>

29:25.430 --> 29:27.465
ALL: [CHANTING]
<i> Drink, drink, drink.</i>

29:27.499 --> 29:29.200
RAYMOND:
<i> Oh, I smell a rumble.</i>
